<body>
        <plainmain>
            <!!!!!!!! These Posts are purely as an example for formatting !!!!!!!!!!>
            <div class="grid-container">
                            <div class="Posts"><br>
                                        <div class="title-text"><b>{{currentPost.title}}</b><br>
                                            {{currentPost.username}} | {{formatDate currentPost.createdAt}}<br>
                                                <img id="viewFullImage" src="/{{currentPost.image}}"><br>
                                             {{currentPost.description}}
                                        </div>
                            </div>

                        <!Area to submit a comment>
                            <div class="commentForm">
                                <form id="CommentForm">
                                <label for="PostComment">Enter a Comment:</label><br>
                                    <textarea rows="23" cols="60" placeholder="Comment here"></textarea> <br>
                                    <input type="submit"><br>
                                </form>
                            </div>
            </div>

            <!Example comments to showcase the formatting>
            <div class="commentForm"> This is example text to show off where the comments will go.</div>
            <div class="commentForm"> This is another comment!</div>
            <div class="commentForm"> Wow! A third comment!</div>
            <div class="commentForm"> I can't believe we got 4 comments on this post! way to go! that's a lot of comments to get on a post! I'm going to make this comment extra long to showcase what it will look like when there's long comments in this comment section!</div>
            <br>

        </plainmain>
</body>
